to the editor re is there a place for ddt by henry i miller op ed aug 7 the only place for ddt is on the list of banned substances ddt is a chlorinated hydrocarbon a dangerous chemical that has been proven to have adverse effects on the nervous and reproductive systems of humans and animals instead of returning to ddt we should seek nonchemical pest controls and support the mosquito 's natural predators i recommend that dr miller dust off his old copy of silent spring and read it in a place where he can hear birds singing amy phalon chatham nj aug 7 2003

